\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. B. variegata} Boiss. & Reuter in Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  3}({\b 1}): 44 (1853) ({\i B. laevigata }auct. hisp. pro parte, non L.). Rhizome woody, covered with remains of old leaves; stems 40-70 cm. Basal leaves laxly rosulate, obovate to obovate-oblong, more or less abruptly contracted into petiole, regularly and deeply toothed or irregularly sinuate-dentate or crenate, pubescent or subglabrous; cauline leaves semi-amplexicaul. Sepals 2-2·5 mm; petals 4-5 mm. Silicula 5-7 × 7·5-10 mm. 2n = 54.{\i  Dry places and mountain rocks. • S. Spain}. Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. B. megacarpaea} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i loc. cit}. (1853). Stems up to 1 m. Basal leaves 7-10(-20) x 2-2·5(-6) cm, densely rosulate, sinuate-dentate, attenuate into petiole, with long and short hairs on upper surface; cauline leaves few, the lower resembling the basal in shape and size, abruptly decreasing in size at about the middle of the stem, the upper linear, entire. Sepals 3-4 mm; petals 6-8 mm. Silicula 8-13 × 13-20 mm. 2n = 54.{\i  Limestone rocks. • S. Spain.} Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. B. foliosa} Mach.-Laur.,{\i  Bot. Arch. }({\i Konigsberg}) {\b 13}: 97 (1926). Like {\b 5} but basal leaves not rosulate, up to 6 × 1-2 cm, remotely and regularly toothed; cauline leaves numerous; silicula 5-8 × 10-12 mm. 2n = 54.{\i  Crevices of limestone rocks. • S.W. Spain} ({\i Serrania de Ronda}). Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. B. gredensis} Guinea, {\i Anal. Inst. Bot. Cavanilles}{\b  21}: 398 (1963). Stems up to 30 cm, erect, pubescent. Basal leaves polymorphic, spathulate, triangular or lanceolate, entire, 2-dentate or 2- to 4-lobulate, the apex obtuse; cauline leaves few, oblong to oblanceolate, entire or toothed. Raceme very long. Sepals 2 mm; petals 4 mm. Silicula 6 × 10 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Granite rocks. • W.C. Spain} ({\i Sierra de Gredos}). Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. B. neustriaca} Bonnet,{\i  Bull. Soc. Dauph. Ech. Pl}{\b . 6}: 222 (1879). Stems 20-40 cm, simple or branched. Basal leaves 4-8 × 1-1·5 cm, erect, spathulate, slightly sinuate-dentate with 3 more or less equal teeth on each side, pubescent or villous, attenuate into a long petiole; cauline leaves broad, entire or dentate. Raceme dense, compact in flower, elongating in fruit. Sepals 2-5 mm; petals 4 mm. Silicula 6-7 × 10-11 mm. •{\i  N.E. France }({\i Seine Valley}). Ga.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. B. frutescens} Cosson, {\i Not. Pl. Crit.} 27 (1849) ({\i B. 'suffrutescens' }Willk., sphalm.). Rhizome black, woody; whole plant covered with dense, white tomentum; stems simple or branched, up to 50 cm. Basal leaves 20 × 6 cm, ovate and sinuate-dentate or lyrate; cauline leaves sessile or amplexicaul, the lower resembling the basal leaves. Inflorescence much-branched. Sepals 2 mm; petals 4 mm. Silicula 3·5-4 × 7 mm, with oblique valves, the margin continuous, with small swellings. 2n = 18.{\i  S.W. Spain; Islas Baleares.} Bl Hs.
\par

