\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. B. vincentina} (Samp.) Rothm. ex Guinea,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  69}: 148 (1964) ({\i B. laevigata} prol. {\i vincentina} Samp.). Rhizome thick, woody; stems 20-30 cm, erect. Basal leaves 5-6 × 1·5-2·5 cm, numerous, densely rosulate, obovate to obovate-oblong, sinuate-undulate, tomentose; cauline leaves minute. Raceme dense, elongating in fruit. Sepals 4 mm; petals 6 mm. Silicula very large, 9-11 × 16-19 mm, with a membranous margin.{\i  Sandy soil. • S.W. Portugal.} Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. B. sempervirens} L., {\i Mantissa Alt.} 255 (1771) (incl. {\i B. montana} Cav.,{\i  B. tomentosa }Lag. ex DC.,{\i  B. rosularis} Boiss. & Reuter,{\i  B. gibraltarica }Wilmott ex Guinea, {\i B. laevigata} auct. hisp. pro parte). Rhizome thick, woody, simple or branched, producing 1-several rosettes of leaves; stems up to 50 cm, simple or branched. Basal leaves 3-12 × 1-5 cm, oblong-lanceolate to broadly obovate or elliptic-spathulate, subentire to deeply sinuate-dentate, usually densely villous or tomentose; cauline leaves few, the lower resembling the basal in size and shape, the upper minute, linear. Raceme more or less dense-flowered. Sepals 3-3·5 mm; petals 5-7 mm. Silicula 4-7 × 7·5-12 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Limestone rocks. S. & S.E. Spain; Islas Baleares.} Bl Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. B. glacialis} (Boiss. & Reuter) Jordan,{\i  Diagn. }{\b 1}({\b 1}): 310 (1864) ({\i B. sempervirens} auct., non L.,{\i  B. secunda} Jordan). Rhizome long, thick and woody; stems 7-15 cm. Basal leaves 1-3 × 0·5 cm, densely rosulate, usually narrowly linear, rarely oblong, densely villous, the apex obtuse; cauline leaves 1-3, minute. Silicula 3 × 6 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Mountains of S. Spain.} Hs.
